The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Deep, Paras for Mumbai meeting

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Regular Bengal captain Deep Dasgupta wants the stars to participate in the domestic circuit more often. He will suggest so at the Ranji Trophy captains and coaches meet to be held in Mumbai on April 20. 

If I am asked to attend the meeting, I will raise the issue of having players like Sachin (Tendulkar), Sourav (Ganguly), Rahul (Dravid) and others to take part in the domestic circuit more often It will benefit the youngsters immensely, Deep told The Telegraph. 

CAB joint secretary Saradindu Pal informed that being the regular captain of the side Deep will represent Bengal along with coach Paras Mhambrey. 

